PROPRIETARY COMPONENTS

The following are NOT open-source and are owned exclusively by Orthalytix SRL:

1. COMPOSITE SCORING ENGINE
   The calibrated biomechanical scoring formula, including:
   - Exact sub-score weighting coefficients (biomechanics, staging,
     attachments, IPR, occlusion, predictability)
   - Severity penalty multipliers and threshold values
   - Grade assignment thresholds

2. CLINICAL MOVEMENT LIMIT DATABASE
   The per-tooth-type movement limits and predictability scores derived
   from proprietary analysis of the clinical literature and internal
   calibration studies. While the general framework is described in the
   published manuscript (arXiv:2603.00124v2), the precise numerical
   parameters are proprietary.

3. STAGING RULE PARAMETERS
   Extrusion deferral thresholds, over-engineering factors, per-aligner
   movement budgets, and anchorage loss heuristics.

4. PRE-TRAINED MODEL WEIGHTS
   All checkpoint files (.pt, .onnx, .safetensors) produced by training
   DGCNN or CHaRM on dental scan datasets.

5. TRAINING PIPELINE
   Data preprocessing pipelines, augmentation strategies, training
   schedules, curriculum learning configurations, and fine-tuning
   procedures used to produce the production model weights.

